metadata.title: Buchanan Solid Pewter Scottish Clan Crest Key Chain/Key Ring
features: Scottish craftsmen made these Clan Crest Key Chains from solid, lead-free pewter.
The clan crest and motto are on the front and the English motto is listed again on the back.
Scottish clans originated in the Highlands. Each one originally identifies with a specific area of Scotland and an individual Clan Chief.

These clan crest key chains are a perfect way to show your Scottish roots. A Scottish clan is a kinship group among the Scottish people. Clans give a sense of shared identity and descent to members, and in modern times have an official structure recognized by the Court of the Lord Lyon, which regulates Scottish heraldry and coats of arms.
Family owned and operated in the USA
